The '''RMIT (Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology) School of Science''' is an [[Australia]]n [[tertiary education]] school within the College of Science Engineering and Health of [[RMIT University]]. It was created in 2016 from the former schools of [[RMIT School of Applied Sciences|Applied Sciences]], [[RMIT School of Computer Science and Information Technology|Computer Science and Information Technology]], and [[RMIT School of Mathematical and Geospatial Sciences|Mathematical and Geospatial Sciences]].
